SIMPLE: numeral
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Numeral
<hw>Nu"mer*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>numeralis</ets>, fr. <ets>numerus</ets> number: cf. F.
<ets>num⟦eacute⟧ral</ets>. See <er>Number</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to number; consisting of number or
numerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A long train of <qex>numeral</qex> progressions.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expressing number; representing number; <as>as,
<ex>numeral</ex> letters or characters, as X or 10 for
ten</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Numeral</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Numeral
<hw>Nu"mer*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A figure or character
used to express a number; <as>as, the Arabic <ex>numerals</ex>, 1, 2, 3,
etc.; the Roman <ex>numerals</ex>, I, V, X, L, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A word expressing a number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Numerally</ent>⟦br⟧
